`fetch_avg_volume`, `fetch_iv_rv_ratio`, `fetch_historical_earnings_dates`, `_nearest_close`, `fetch_atm_straddle_price` each open/close their own connection even when called back-to-back for the same symbol in `evaluate_symbol`/`run_candidate_scan`. Dolt/MySQL connection setup isn't free, especially repeated dozens of times per symbol across a nightly scan of many symbols.

**Fix**: introduce a small `_dolt_connect` context manager cached per-database for the duration of a scan run (a connection pool of one connection per database name, reused across calls within `get_ranked_symbols`), e.g.:

```python
_conn_cache: dict[str, "mysql.connector.MySQLConnection"] = {}

def _dolt_connect(config, database):
    if database not in _conn_cache or not _conn_cache[database].is_connected():
        _conn_cache[database] = mysql.connector.connect(..., database=database)
    return _conn_cache[database]
```
(Close all cached connections at the end of `cmd_get_ranked_symbols`/`run_candidate_scan`.)

